Aap Linux mein commands ka use karke yeh jaan sakte hain ki kaunsa server running hai aur uski utilization kitni hai. Niche kuch commonly used commands diye gaye hain:

1. Server Running Status Check

uptime: Yeh command system uptime aur load average batati hai.

uptime

top: Real-time mein running processes aur resource utilization dekhne ke liye.

top

ps: Specific services ya processes check karne ke liye.

ps aux | grep <service-name>

systemctl: Service status check karne ke liye.

systemctl status <service-name>


2. Utilization Check

CPU Utilization:

mpstat

Memory Utilization:

free -h

Disk Utilization:

df -h

I/O Utilization:

iostat

Network Utilization:

iftop


3. Combine Server and Utilization Information

CPU and Memory usage:

top -b -n1 | head -n 15

Specific process utilization:

ps aux --sort=-%cpu | head -n 10

Load average:

cat /proc/loadavg


Yeh commands apko server ke running hone aur resource utilization ki detail provide karengi. Agar aapko output ka analysis karna hai ya automation karni ho, toh cron, bash scripting, ya tools like Nagios aur Zabbix ka use kar sakte hain.
